ounting 5.4 billion k-mers.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999722242355347}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.7894973754882812e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "We show that BLight can index massive k-mer sets from raw NGS datasets, either from metagenomics or transcriptomic samples, up to an enormous soil sample containing more than 19 billion distinct k-mers.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004547119140625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0055811405181884766}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "We also used BLight to associate to each k-mer its number of occurrences across the datasets to show a library's straightforward application.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.67572021484375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "We show that BLight constructs its index using substantially less memory than Pufferfish construction steps and the Pufferfish index itself.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9807851314544678}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.001544952392578125}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "For example, BLight is successfully integrated as an indexing structure in REINDEER [14], a k-mer data structure that enables the quantification of query sequences in thousands of raw read samples.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.137920379638672e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004863083362579346}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "We wrote the BLight index as an open source C++ library under the AGPL3 license available at github.com/Malfoy/BLight.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2665868401527405}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.006243109703063965}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744680523872375}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Blight", "normalizedForm": "Blight", "offsetStart": 14, "offsetEnd": 20}, "context": "However, here Blight performs a query for each k-mer of the dataset to count its abundance, representing an excessive construction time. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004701793193817139}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.491474151611328e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998243451118469}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992128610610962}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 15, "offsetEnd": 21}, "context": "We showed that BLight can index the largest available genomes to date using a reasonable amount of memory while outperforming state of the art methods in both construction time and memory.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.07372117042541504}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00040596723556518555}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPSS", "normalizedForm": "SPSS", "offsetStart": 16, "offsetEnd": 20}, "context": "Unitigs are one SPSS, super-k-mers of unitigs are another [14].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.005179882049560547}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.2993812561035156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.999995231628418}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999356269836426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "[21]", "normalizedForm": "[21]", "refKey": 21}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 18, "offsetEnd": 24}, "context": "We point out that BLight can directly work on any SPSS formatted in FASTA format to mitigate this downside as we can build the super-k-mers from any set of sequences without duplicated k-mers. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005353093147277832}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0124284029006958}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPSS", "normalizedForm": "SPSS", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 23}, "context": "In the literature, SPSS narrow this definition to the representation of a k-mer set and forget the k-mer multiplicities.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00028771162033081055}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.372264862060547e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.999995231628418}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999356269836426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "[21]", "normalizedForm": "[21]", "refKey": 21}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 25}, "context": "We constructed the BLight index on the previously mentioned genomes graphs with several minimizer sizes to assess the minimizer size's impact.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997844099998474}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9974281191825867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 20, "offsetEnd": 26}, "context": "the memory usage of BLight is significantly reduced compared to the other methods, the index construction is way slower than SRC or Squeakr.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013265609741210938}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.127357482910156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Blight", "normalizedForm": "Blight", "offsetStart": 24, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "We built Pufferfish and Blight indexes directly on the compacted de Bruijn graphs to ensure a fair comparison.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.10374003648757935}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992128610610962}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998243451118469}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9992128610610962}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 24, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "Conversely, we designed BLight with a more generic application range in mind.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.435943603515625e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998741149902344}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 25, "offsetEnd": 31}, "context": "In this work, we propose BLight, a low-cost, high-throughput, and exact associative structure for indexing k-mers, relying on de compacted Bruijn graphs or other efficient SPSS.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.127357482910156e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999356269836426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "We compare a simple usage of BLight through a k-mer abundance index snippet, with two methods from state-of-the-art that allow large scale k-mer to abundance association.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0009819269180297852}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.119510650634766e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "environment", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPSS", "normalizedForm": "SPSS", "offsetStart": 38, "offsetEnd": 42}, "context": "This table shows the benefit of using SPSS to represent and index k-mer set more concisely and how BLight can benefit from those approaches. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0016204118728637695}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.1205673217773438e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.999995231628418}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999356269836426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "[21]", "normalizedForm": "[21]", "refKey": 21}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 40, "offsetEnd": 46}, "context": "We could implement this strategy in the BLight index, but we favor our scheme for simplicity and efficiency with low sub-sampling ratios.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.02113884687423706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8286657929420471}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Bcalm", "normalizedForm": "Bcalm", "offsetStart": 41, "offsetEnd": 46}, "version": {"rawForm": "2", "normalizedForm": "2"}, "context": "They can be constructed efficiently with Bcalm2 [20] from any FASTA/FASTQ file compressed or not.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.013964533805847168}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.3484230041503906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999806880950928}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.017941772937774658}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "[20]", "normalizedForm": "[20]", "refKey": 20, "offsetStart": 8214, "offsetEnd": 8218}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 41, "offsetEnd": 47}, "context": "For now, we assume that we construct the BLight index from the unitigs of the compacted de Bruijn graph constructed from a k-mer set.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997668862342834}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.20843058824539185}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SPSS", "normalizedForm": "SPSS", "offsetStart": 42, "offsetEnd": 46}, "context": "Recently, spectrumpreserving string sets (SPSS) [21] were defined as an exact representation of a multiset of k-mers coming from a set of strings of length \u2265 k.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.130682110786438}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.894371032714844e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.999995231628418}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999356269836426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "references": [{"label": "[21]", "normalizedForm": "[21]", "refKey": 21, "offsetStart": 4553, "offsetEnd": 4557}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 49}, "context": "BLight as a de Bruijn graph representation BLight can be used as a high-throughput de Bruijn graph representation but is not competitive compared to space-efficient graph structures.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.4226646423339844e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.6133995056152344e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 45, "offsetEnd": 51}, "context": "We summarized the best results obtained with BLight compared to Pufferfish in Table 1.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999785423278809}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.0848045349121094e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999927282333374}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999411106109619}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9744681715965271}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "BLight", "normalizedForm": "BLight", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 52}, "context": "Benefit of Spectrum-preserving string sets In BLight, our first choice was to represent k-mer sets in an exact and partitioned way using super-k-mers from unitigs.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9635010361671448}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.015606105327606201}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"u